messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /clients/{id}

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

Acceptable methods (based on the code, not assumptions):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: true

Explanation:
- In index.js the clients router is mounted with app.use('/clients', clientRoutes), so every route in routes/clients.js is prefixed with /clients.
- In routes/clients.js the route for the controller updateClient is declared as router.patch('/:id', updateClient). Combining the mount path and the router path yields /clients/:id, expressed as /clients/{id}.
- Only routes explicitly registered for the same path segment are router.patch('/:id', updateClient) and router.delete('/:id', deleteClient). Therefore PATCH and DELETE are acceptable for /clients/{id}.
- There is no explicit GET, PUT, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, or HEAD handler for /clients/:id in the provided routing code. Although a getClient controller exists, it is not wired into the router, so GET is not accepted for this path according to the code. OPTIONS and HEAD are not explicitly defined either, so per the instruction to base answers on the code (not runtime behavior or middleware defaults like CORS/Express automatic HEAD handling), they are marked false.
- "All HTTP methods acceptable" is false because the router registers only particular methods (PATCH and DELETE) for this path.
